description: More than 1,000 people have been killed in two weeks of intensifying Israeli strikes against Hezbollah and hundreds of thousands have been displaced.
title: Israel’s escalating war in Lebanon brings calamity to a fragile state

description: Austria’s Freedom Party leads in the vote count, but may not be able find coalition partners to form a government under provocative leader Herbert Kickl.
title: Austrian far right set to win national election, in post-war first

description: The severity of Israel’s attacks have called into question the very reason for the organization's existence, which was predicated on deterring Israeli attacks against Lebanon and Iran.
title: Nasrallah’s assassination shreds illusion of Hezbollah’s military might

description: Momentum for further action is building in Israel, where many believe their country has gained an upper hand against a longtime foe and should make the most of its advantage.
title: Israelis cheer Nasrallah assassination but are wary of what comes next

description: Videos shared by the IDF show fighter jets they say were involved in the Nasrallah operation carrying BLU-109s, an American-made 2,000-pound munition.
title: Israel likely used U.S.-made 2,000-pound bombs in Nasrallah strike, visuals show

description: A Catholic university took the rare step of criticizing Pope Francis, saying that he called women “a fertile welcome, care, vital devotion.”
title: Pope criticized for giving ‘reductive’ view on women’s role in society

description: Britain was a country powered by coal. Now it’s the first G-7 nation to quit it. In a matter of hours, the boilers at the Ratcliffe plant will cool to the touch.
title: U.K., home of the industrial revolution, shuts its last coal-fired power plant

description: The deaths of Yaroslav Bazylevych’s whole family — killed in Lviv by a Russian hypersonic missile — proved there was no sanctuary from the war.
title: It was Ukraine’s ‘safe’ city. Then his whole family died.

description: The IDF said it targeted dozens of Hezbollah targets early Sunday. Some countries urged citizens to leave Lebanon, as it braces for a possible ground invasion.
title: Live updates: Israel continues strikes after over 1,000 killed in 2 weeks in Lebanon
